---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="Agents"
	description="How OrgOps agents collaborate in channels: scoped context, explicit tools, and traceable actions."
>
	<header class="hero">
		<h1>Agents</h1>
		<p class="lede">
			OrgOps agents are collaborators that operate inside channels, follow coordination rules, and interact with the
			system through events.
		</p>
	</header>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>How agents work here</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Scoped context:</strong> agents act within a channel’s conversation and memory.</li>
			<li><strong>Explicit tools:</strong> side effects happen via tool calls and command envelopes.</li>
			<li><strong>Traceability:</strong> actions are recorded as events for audit and debugging.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Coordination patterns</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Delegate work by @mentioning another agent in a shared channel.</li>
			<li>Use scheduled triggers for delayed follow-ups.</li>
			<li>Keep long-running workstreams in dedicated channels.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.lede {
		max-width: 70ch;
		color: rgb(var(--muted));
	}
	.section {
		margin-top: 2.25rem;
		max-width: 75ch;
	}
</style>
